# S3 CLI Tool

A simple Python Command-Line Interface (CLI) for managing AWS S3 buckets and objects.  

This tool allows you to perform common S3 operations like creating buckets, uploading/downloading files, applying public read policies, and deleting buckets with all contents â€” all from your terminal.

---

## Features

- Create new S3 buckets in any AWS region
- List all existing buckets
- Upload files to a bucket (with optional object name)
- Download files from a bucket
- Apply a public read policy to a bucket
- Delete buckets along with all files inside
- Interactive, menu-driven CLI for ease of use

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.x  
- [Boto3](https://pypi.org/project/boto3/) library  

Install Boto3 using pip:

```bash
pip install boto3
